ReLU stands for:

Rectified Linear Unit

It is one of the most commonly used activation functions in Deep Learning.

=====


Formula

ReLU(x)=max(0,x)

=========


Simple Meaning

ReLU checks the input value:

If value is positive → keep it same
If value is negative → convert to 0

======
Working Rule

| Input (x) | Output |
| --------- | ------ |
| x > 0     | x      |
| x < 0     | 0      |


========

Example 1 (Positive Value)
Input = 8

Calculation:

ReLU = max(0, 8)
= 8

Output:

8
Example 2 (Negative Value)
Input = -5

Calculation:

ReLU = max(0, -5)
= 0

Output:

0
Graph Meaning

The ReLU graph works like this:

Negative side → flat at 0
Positive side → straight line
Negative Inputs → 0
Positive Inputs → Same Value
Why ReLU is Important?

ReLU helps neural networks:

Learn faster
Reduce complexity
Avoid vanishing gradient problem
Improve Deep Learning performance

===========

Real-Time Example
Student Marks Filtering

Suppose:

Negative marks are not allowed

If score becomes:

-3

ReLU converts it to:

0

If score is:

7

ReLU keeps:

7
ANN Flow with ReLU
Input
  ↓
Weights Applied
  ↓
Net Input
  ↓
ReLU Activation Function
  ↓
Output
====


Advantages of ReLU

| Advantage | Meaning                       |
| --------- | ----------------------------- |
| Simple    | Easy calculation              |
| Fast      | Faster training               |
| Efficient | Works well in deep networks   |
| Popular   | Most used activation function |


============

Limitation

Sometimes neurons may stop learning if output always becomes 0.

This is called:

Dying ReLU Problem

============

One-Line Definition
ReLU is an activation function that returns the input value if positive, otherwise returns 0.

